"On the contrary, it has come to our attention that some politicians have turned to both mainstream and social media to accuse and counter-accuse their opponents, and further drag the commission and its staff in their propagandist pronouncements," reads a statement by IEBC.
"The commission urges leaders and members of the public to maintain peace and report any election-related malpractices to the respective returning officers for necessary action."
Smooth exercises
The IEBC further noted that save for the allegations of voter intimidation and bribery in Msambweni, all the seven by-elections held on Tuesday went on smoothly.





The six other areas wher by-elections were conducted were Dabaso, Mbale, Kisumu North, Lakeview, Kahawa-Wendani and Gaturi.
In Msambweni, the two main rivals are ODM candidate Omar Boga and independent candidate Feisal Bader, who traded accusations.
Mr Bader is backed by Deputy President William Ruto's allies, who have accused security officers of siding with their rivals in the Orange Democratic Movement and letting them bribe and intimidate voters.
The DP's allies have, however not given any evidence to support their claims, but former Machakos Senator Johnson Muthama and Belgut MP Nelson Koech were arrested earlier on Tuesday.



