Mr Muthama was detained at Port Police Station while Mr Koech was taken to the Likoni ferry police post in Mombasa.
The two were accused of causing chaos during the vote in Msambweni.
Police bosses declined to comment on their arrests.
Meanwhile, Mr Boga has accused Nyali MP Mohamed Ali of causing tension during the mini-poll.
"We are aware that they are creating tension in my strongholds so that people do not turn up. I assure my people that the situation is under control. Police have assured us of total security,” he said at Jogoo grounds.
